# Configuration

Manages project configuration stored in `.intentc/config.yaml`. Includes agent profile types, config loading/saving, merging with CLI overrides, and schema validation.

## Agent Profile Types

### AgentProfile

Named, reusable agent configuration.

- `Name` (string) - Profile identifier.
- `Provider` (string) - `"claude"`, `"codex"`, or `"cli"`.
- `Command` (string) - Shell command for CLI provider.
- `CLIArgs` (list of strings) - Additional CLI arguments.
- `Timeout` (duration) - Agent invocation timeout. Default 5m.
- `Retries` (integer) - Retry count. Default 3.
- `RateLimit` (duration) - Delay between retries. Default 1s.
- `ModelID` (string, optional) - Provider-specific model identifier.
- `PromptTemplates` (PromptTemplates, optional) - Template overrides.
- `Tools` (list of ToolConfig, optional) - Tool configurations.
- `Skills` (list of strings, optional) - Named skills.

### PromptTemplates

- `Build` (string) - Template for build prompts.
- `Validate` (string) - Template for validation prompts.
- `System` (string) - System prompt for all invocations.

### ToolConfig

- `Name` (string) - Tool identifier.
- `Enabled` (boolean) - Default true.
- `Config` (map) - Tool-specific configuration.

## Config

```
Config:
  Version: integer
  Profiles: map of string to AgentProfile  # Must contain "default"
  Build:
    DefaultOutput: string                   # Default "build-default"
  Logging:
    Level: string                           # debug, info, warn, error. Default "info"
```

## Functions

- `GetDefaultConfig()` - Returns config with sensible defaults (Claude provider, 5m timeout, 3 retries).
- `LoadConfig(projectRoot)` - Load from `.intentc/config.yaml`. Return defaults if file missing.
- `SaveConfig(projectRoot, config)` - Write config to disk.
- `MergeConfig(base, override)` - Non-zero override fields win. Per-profile merging.
- `GetProfile(cfg, name)` - Look up profile by name. Empty name falls back to "default".
- `ValidateConfig(cfg)` - Returns list of SchemaViolation. Checks: version present, "default" profile exists, valid provider values, CLI profiles have command.
